post_text:
This picture represents the seen and unseen:

What you can see:

- Our staff members appropriately wearing their masks.

What you can't see:

-The smile on their faces...we have missed our students!

-The hours and hours and hours of hard work our teachers and support staff have put into making sure students will learn, regardless of the platform or circumstances.

-Our staff's commitment to making sure that our school-wide safety protocols are taught and followed by everyone in the building.

-Our families and their help to ensure that students are prepared for the first day of the school year.

This is hard for everyone - students, parents, staff. But we can’t wait to get started! #WeAreInThisTogether #WeAreUSD231

We will update this page throughout the summer so check back often for additional information.

shared_text:
Gardner Edgerton Youth and Community Programs
June 18 at 3:02 PM ·

Welcome to Virtual Summer Enrichment! GEYCP is excited to offer something new for your child this summer when face-to-face instruction isn’t an option. GEYCP and USD 231 staff members will be providing you with engaging lessons in Art, STEM, and Athletics.

Currently, GEHS Art Teachers, Mrs. Britt and Mrs. McCormick, have two different art projects and GEHS Basketball coaches, Coach Leiker and Coach White, have some fun drills to do in your driveway!

GEYCP encourages you to share your final results with us and you could find your final product showcased on social media or in a video. You can submit your final pictures or video to GEYCP@usd231.com or through social media!

We will be adding new content early next week!

ENJOY AND HAVE FUN!!!

View the activities here: https://bit.ly/2N7ikGs

shared_text:
USD 231 Nutrition Services
June 17 at 9:11 AM ·

🥳🤩HELD OVER!!🥳🤩 We are thrilled to share that the USDA waiver for our site has been extended and we will be continuing weekly curbside meals through July 27!

"Kid-less" pickup still available and there is no need to re-register. If you still need to do this, click here >> https://bit.ly/2yzBeSq

Same times, same places EXCEPT the week of JULY 6. (Distribution for this week (only) will be Wednesday 7/8 at all sites and consist of 3 breakfasts/3 lunches. This will give our team a much-needed break over the July 4 holiday!) All other weeks are Mondays as scheduled through July 27.

Thank you to all of our families for your continued support! We <3 seeing our kids in the loop each week and are overjoyed this will continue through the summer!

Gardner Edgerton School District

post_text:
Superintendent Pam Stranathan and USD 231 recognize the disappointment faced by our seniors and their families over the many special events canceled this Spring due to COVID-19.

As a token of appreciation and recognition for the class of 2020, Mrs. Stranathan personally reached out to PEC sports, a locally owned business, and is partnering with them to provide every senior a personalized yard sign that will include a picture and graduation year. The cost of the yard signs will be covered by the school district.

Please know the district will continue to plan for events as allowed by the state and local health department; however, we fully understand these types of activities will never replace rites of passage such as prom, graduation, and many others.

USD 231 is very proud of each and every one of our seniors!

Please visit this site for the full story (https://www.usd231.com/article/226863?org=district).

post_text: This looks like a fairly empty room; however, we are modeling social distancing while working with over 65 of our teachers to finalize the details of of our Continuous Learning Plan. The plan will be focused on student learning opportunities through experiences that focus on key concepts, knowledge, and skills. These opportunities will emphasize interaction and creativity and involve a balance of on-screen and off-screen tasks that help students connect to previous, current, and new learning!

post_text: IMPORTANT NOTICE! Please pay close attention to the number of food kits per site.
shared_text:
USD 231 Nutrition Services
March 25 at 8:30 AM ·

We can’t wait to see everyone again today!

Please note that we have increased the number of meals we have available, but wanted to give everyone a heads up as to the number of meals we have available at each site for today.

Edgerton Elem - 400 kits
Trail Ridge MS - 1000 kits
Wheatridge MS - 1000 kits
(up 300 total from Monday)

Our team has been working non-stop to meet the needs of our community, but with every district providing similar services, we are experiencing a demand greater than our supply chain’s capacity - just like the grocery stores. We are getting shipments daily to restock our supply and packing as quickly as our 10-person per building teams can possibly work. We ask that you please be patient with our team and each other today! 😊

post_text:
In the event USD 231 closes school due to inclement weather or other school-related closures, the information is communicated as soon as the decision is made in the following ways:

- Posted on our website - www.usd231.org
- Posted to social media (Facebook/Twitter/Instagram?)
- Local television stations (ABC, CBS, FOX, NBC) (**Please know we are at the mercy of these stations as to whether or not they relay the information. There have been instances of when the district has provided information and the news station did not get it posted.)
- USD 231 App (Andriod and Apple)

Our inclement weather procedures can be found here: https://www.usd231.com/o/district/page/inclement-weather-procedures

Thank you for your continued support and understanding.

Due to the inclement weather forecast, please know the following decisions have been made related to district activities and facilities:

- Friday, January 10 - All evening events have been canceled (practice, clubs, games, etc after 6:00pm). All facility rentals have been canceled.
- Saturday, January 11 - All events have been canceled (practices, clubs, etc.). All facility rentals have been canceled. GEHS activities already on location (Wichita and Dodge City) will make a decision on Saturday related to returning. If roads are unsafe, they will secure hotel rooms for an additional night.
- Sunday, January 12 - All events have been canceled (practices, clubs, etc.). All facility rentals have been canceled.

Emily Baden, a fourth-grade teacher at Nike Elementary, has been recognized by the Kansas State Department of Education as an outstanding first-year teacher. Dr. Randy Watson, Commissioner of Education, called to congratulate Emily on January 7, 2020. The Horizon Award is reserved for those teachers who have successfully completed their first year of teaching and have performed in such a way as to distinguish themselves as outstanding.

Press Release and Video can be found here: http://bit.ly/2T4XU4Z

post_text: On Tuesday, December 10, the United Community Services of Johnson County Annual Meeting and Awards Ceremony was held at Johnson County Community College. Superintendent Pam Stranathan, along with the other Johnson County Superintendents, and teen council members were the recipients of the Excellence in Community Service award for their efforts with Zero Reasons Why. Gardner Edgerton High School teen council representatives Hanna and Abigail Thomas were also on hand to receive the award. Congratulations on your continued efforts to help with mental health awareness. #WeAreUSD231
